──── 1A. SITEMAP ──────────────────────────────────────────

File: app/sitemap.ts

Next.js 15 generates sitemap.xml automatically from this
file. Export a default async function that returns a
MetadataRoute.Sitemap array.

Include these URL groups:

  STATIC ROUTES (priority + changeFrequency):
    /              priority: 1.0   changeFreq: monthly
    /projects      priority: 0.9   changeFreq: monthly
    /blog          priority: 0.8   changeFreq: weekly

  DYNAMIC — PROJECT PAGES:
    Import projects from data/projects.ts
    Map each to:
      url:             `${siteConfig.url}/projects/${p.slug}`
      lastModified:    new Date(p.year, 11, 31)
      priority:        0.7
      changeFrequency: 'yearly'

  DYNAMIC — BLOG POST PAGES:
    Import getAllPosts from lib/mdx.ts
    const posts = getAllPosts()
    Map each to:
      url:             `${siteConfig.url}/blog/${p.slug}`
      lastModified:    new Date(p.date)
      priority:        0.6
      changeFrequency: 'never'
      (posts don't change once published)

Full return shape per entry:
  {
    url:             string (absolute URL with https://)
    lastModified:    Date
    changeFrequency: 'always'|'hourly'|'daily'|'weekly'|
                     'monthly'|'yearly'|'never'
    priority:        number (0.0 – 1.0)
  }

After deploy, verify sitemap at:
  https://yourname.dev/sitemap.xml

