──── 3D. CORE WEB VITALS TARGETS ─────────────────────────

These are the metrics Google uses for search ranking.
Verify each after running pnpm build && pnpm start:

  LCP (Largest Contentful Paint): < 2.5s
    The LCP element on the homepage is almost always the
    hero section heading or the code card image.
    If LCP > 2.5s: check that the hero image (if any)
    has priority={true} and is properly sized.

  CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift): < 0.1
    The most common cause in portfolios: images without
    explicit width/height causing reflow on load.
    Fix: every next/image either has explicit w/h or
    uses the fill prop with a sized container.

  FID/INP (Interaction to Next Paint): < 200ms
    The most common cause: heavy JS executing on the
    main thread during page load.
    Fix: verified in bundle analysis step above.

  FCP (First Contentful Paint): < 1.8s
    The most common cause: render-blocking resources
    (fonts, CSS). next/font with display:swap fixes fonts.
    Tailwind CSS is purged at build time — no issue.

Run PageSpeed Insights after deploy:
  https://pagespeed.web.dev/
  Enter your live URL. Both Mobile and Desktop must
  pass. Mobile is harder — prioritize it first.

