PART 4 — ANALYTICS (PRIVACY-FIRST)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Using Vercel Analytics — zero configuration, no cookie
banner needed, GDPR compliant by default, free on
Vercel's hobby plan.

DO NOT use Google Analytics. It requires a cookie consent
banner, adds 45KB to the bundle, and sends visitor data
to Google. For a portfolio, Vercel Analytics gives all
the data you actually need (page views, top pages,
referrers, countries) with none of the downsides.

──── 4A. INSTALL ──────────────────────────────────────────

  pnpm add @vercel/analytics @vercel/speed-insights

──── 4B. ADD TO ROOT LAYOUT ───────────────────────────────

File: app/layout.tsx

  import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'
  import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'

  // Inside the root layout's return, just before </body>:
  <Analytics />
  <SpeedInsights />

Both components:
  - Are tree-shaken to zero bytes in non-Vercel environments
  - Add ~1KB to the bundle when deployed on Vercel
  - Collect no personally identifiable information
  - Require no configuration, no API key, no env var

SpeedInsights collects real-user Core Web Vitals data
from actual visitors — more valuable than synthetic
Lighthouse scores because it shows real-world performance
on real devices and connections.

