──── 5A. FAVICON SYSTEM ───────────────────────────────────

A proper favicon system in 2025 requires these files.
Do not use a single .ico file — modern browsers and
devices need multiple formats and sizes.

Generate all files from a single source SVG using
realfavicongenerator.net (free). Upload your logo/initials
SVG and download the complete favicon package.

Files to place in /app/ (not /public/):
  favicon.ico         (32×32, for legacy browsers)
  icon.svg            (scalable, modern browsers)
  icon-192.png        (192×192, Android PWA)
  icon-512.png        (512×512, Android PWA splash)
  apple-icon.png      (180×180, iOS home screen)

Next.js 15 automatically serves these when placed in
/app/ — no configuration needed. The filenames are
a Next.js convention.

File: app/icon.tsx (alternative to static icon.svg)
If you want to generate the favicon programmatically
(useful to keep it consistent with your primary color):

  import { ImageResponse } from 'next/og'

  export const runtime = 'edge'
  export const size = { width: 32, height: 32 }
  export const contentType = 'image/png'

  export default function Icon() {
    return new ImageResponse(
      <div style={{
        width:        '100%',
        height:       '100%',
        display:      'flex',
        alignItems:   'center',
        justifyContent: 'center',
        background:   '#6366f1',
        borderRadius: '6px',
        fontSize:     '18px',
        fontWeight:   700,
        color:        'white',
        fontFamily:   'system-ui',
      }}>
        H
      </div>,
      { ...size }
    )
  }

  This generates a purple square with "H" (for Hitarth).
  Simple, recognizable, on-brand.

